{"type":"message","id":"3e0500c6","parentId":"22572615","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:57:04.383Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LgLsR0WIjrv1K1slAtClYRcS|fc_0d371f2cfb221f1c0169fbf16fdac88191b8672cf4ab3fda9c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:651:  `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.files.urlAllowlist` and\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:652:  `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.images.urlAllowlist`, and keep `maxUrlParts` low.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:923:- Treat credentials that can call `/v1/chat/completions`, `/v1/responses`, or `/api/channels/*` as full-access operator secrets for that gateway.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:106:- tiny direct `/v1/chat/completions` calls work\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:111:curl http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1/chat/completions \\\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:121:- `model_not_found` or 404 errors even though direct `/v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:129:    - `model_not_found` with a local MLX/vLLM-style server → verify `baseUrl` includes `/v1`, `api` is `\"openai-completions\"` for `/v1/chat/completions` backends, and `models.providers.<provider>.models[].id` is the bare provider-local id. Select it with the provider prefix once, for example `mlx/mlx-community/Qwen3-30B-A3B-6bit`; keep the catalog entry as `mlx-community/Qwen3-30B-A3B-6bit`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md:447:    - `models.providers.*.api`: request adapter (`openai-completions`, `openai-responses`, `anthropic-messages`, `google-generative-ai`, etc). For self-hosted `/v1/chat/completions` backends such as MLX, vLLM, SGLang, and most OpenAI-compatible local servers, use `openai-completions`. A custom provider with `baseUrl` but no `api` defaults to `openai-completions`; set `openai-responses` only when the backend supports `/v1/responses`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:21:Operational behavior matches [OpenAI Chat Completions](/gateway/openai-http-api):\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:49:Enable or disable this endpoint with `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.enabled`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:56:- `POST /v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:58:For the canonical explanation of how agent-target models, `openclaw/default`, embeddings pass-through, and backend model overrides fit together, see [OpenAI Chat Completions](/gateway/openai-http-api#agent-first-model-contract) and [Model list and agent routing](/gateway/openai-http-api#model-list-and-agent-routing).\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:193:Defaults can be tuned under `gateway.http.endpoints.responses`:\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:343:- [OpenAI chat completions](/gateway/openai-http-api)\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/index.md:76:  - HTTP APIs, OpenAI compatible (`/v1/models`, `/v1/embeddings`, `/v1/chat/completions`, `/v1/responses`, `/tools/invoke`)\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/index.md:91:- `POST /v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:481:- Chat Completions: disabled by default. Enable with `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions.enabled: true`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:482:- Responses API: `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.enabled`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:484:  - `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.maxUrlParts`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:485:  - `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.files.urlAllowlist`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:486:  - `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.images.urlAllowlist`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:487:    Empty allowlists are treated as unset; use `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.files.allowUrl=false`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:488:    and/or `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.images.allowUrl=false` to disable URL fetching.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:2:summary: \"Expose an OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions HTTP endpoint from the Gateway\"\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:5:title: \"OpenAI chat completions\"\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:12:- `POST /v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:13:- Same port as the Gateway (WS + HTTP multiplex): `http://<gateway-host>:<port>/v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:99:Set `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions.enabled` to `true`:\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:106:        chatCompletions: { enabled: true },\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:115:Set `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions.enabled` to `false`:\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:122:        chatCompletions: { enabled: false },\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:141:- Existing OpenAI chat clients can usually start with `/v1/chat/completions`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:223:curl -sS http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openai-http-api.md:235:curl -N http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions \\\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/local-models.md:134:gateways work if they expose an OpenAI-style `/v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/local-models.md:330:- Direct tiny `/v1/chat/completions` calls work, but `openclaw infer model run --local`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:651:  `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.files.urlAllowlist` and\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:652:  `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.images.urlAllowlist`, and keep `maxUrlParts` low.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/security/index.md:923:- Treat credentials that can call `/v1/chat/completions`, `/v1/responses`, or `/api/channels/*` as full-access operator secrets for that gateway.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:106:- tiny direct `/v1/chat/completions` calls work\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:111:curl http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1/chat/completions \\\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:121:- `model_not_found` or 404 errors even though direct `/v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/troubleshooting.md:129:    - `model_not_found` with a local MLX/vLLM-style server → verify `baseUrl` includes `/v1`, `api` is `\"openai-completions\"` for `/v1/chat/completions` backends, and `models.providers.<provider>.models[].id` is the bare provider-local id. Select it with the provider prefix once, for example `mlx/mlx-community/Qwen3-30B-A3B-6bit`; keep the catalog entry as `mlx-community/Qwen3-30B-A3B-6bit`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-tools.md:447:    - `models.providers.*.api`: request adapter (`openai-completions`, `openai-responses`, `anthropic-messages`, `google-generative-ai`, etc). For self-hosted `/v1/chat/completions` backends such as MLX, vLLM, SGLang, and most OpenAI-compatible local servers, use `openai-completions`. A custom provider with `baseUrl` but no `api` defaults to `openai-completions`; set `openai-responses` only when the backend supports `/v1/responses`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:21:Operational behavior matches [OpenAI Chat Completions](/gateway/openai-http-api):\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:49:Enable or disable this endpoint with `gateway.http.endpoints.responses.enabled`.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:56:- `POST /v1/chat/completions`\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/openresponses-http-api.md:58:For the canonical explanation of how agent-target models, `openclaw/default`, embeddings pass-through, and backend model overrides fit together, see [OpenAI Chat Completions](/gateway/openai-http-api#agent-first-model-contract) and [Model list and agent routing](/gateway/openai-http-api#model-list-and-agent-routing).\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/d